DBIx::MyParse version 0.20
====================

This module provides access to the MySQL SQL parser.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

	* The MySQL source
	* libmysqld

You can find the MySQL source at 

http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/4.1.html

near the bottom of the page, under the "Source Downloads" heading.

To install the tar.gz source tree, you can use:

$ wget http://mysql.he.net/Downloads/MySQL-4.1/mysql-4.1.13a.tar.gz
$ gzip -d mysql-4.1.13a.tar.gz
$ tar xfv mysql-4.1.13a.tar.gz
$ cd mysql-4.1.13a
$ ./configure --with-embedded-server

To install libmysqld, in case you do not have one already:

$ cd mysql-4.1.13
$ make
$ cd libmysqld
$ make install

